			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For Namco 108 and MMC3, the values are offsets from the beginning of CHR ROM in units of 1024 ($400) bytes. The first two cover 2 KiB regions at $0000-$07FF and $0800-$0FFF; the others cover 1 KiB regions at $1000-$13FF, ..., $1C00-$1FFF. (MMC3 can invert the sense of bit 12 such that the banks instead start at $1000, $1800, $0000, $0400, $0800, and $0C00.) So <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">14 16 00 01 02 03</tt> means switch CHR ROM $05000-$05FFF into PPU $0000 and $00000-$00FFF into PPU $1000.<br /><br />Is a value greater than $1F ever written to $8001? If not, then you could probably just take the existing ROM and run it on TLSROM (mapper 118). If so, you'll need to map values $20-$3F to $80-$9F, and it'll run on TLSROM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

